2. `src/core/compaction.ail:84-112` -- tool-call/tool-result pair matching by `tool_call_id`
3. `src/core/context_usage.ail:12-28` -- token estimation using char-count heuristic (chars / 3.8)
4. `.motoko/config/default/compaction_ai.json` -- default `compact_ratio: 0.95`

[09:15:14.887] The compaction engine uses a three-tier system based on the context window fill ratio:

| Tier | Trigger | Tool Pairs Kept |
|------|---------|-----------------|
| Low | >= 70% full | 40% of pairs |
| Medium | >= 85% full | 20% of pairs |
| High | >= 95% full | 10% of pairs + last 5 non-tool messages |

System messages are always preserved. The tier is selected based on the *current* estimated ratio, not incrementally -- so a sudden spike from 60% to 90% jumps straight to tier M.

